          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"galaga_marimo-examples\">galaga_marimo \u2014 Examples</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">This notebook demonstrates the <code>galaga_marimo</code> helper library for rendering\ngeometric algebra objects in marimo notebooks using Python 3.14 t-strings.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The core idea: interpolate GA objects directly into markdown, and they\nautomatically render as LaTeX. No manual <code>.latex()</code> calls needed.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "bkHC",
      "code_hash": "ab3eb1febd355158020da21a65689e56",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"setup\">Setup</h2></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "lEQa",
      "code_hash": "451bfb74e994259e91053917d8e8010e",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": ""
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "PKri",
      "code_hash": "2b39824d4387d97af26e8795e1fe7d18",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"basic-interpolation\">Basic Interpolation</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Any object with a <code>.latex()</code> method is automatically rendered as inline LaTeX.\nPlain Python values (strings, ints, floats) render as text.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Xref",
      "code_hash": "eb5020ef119be7022b4e5ef866124113",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><ul>\n<li>A vector: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(3 e_{1} + 2 e_{2} - e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>A basis vector: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(e_{1}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>A bivector: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(e_{12}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>A rotor: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(0.939373 - 0.342898 e_{12}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>A plain string: hello</li>\n<li>An integer: 42</li>\n<li>A float: 3.14</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "SFPL",
      "code_hash": "8883dce1dcd4deb84847924bd8522286",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"format-specs\">Format Specs</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Use format specs to control rendering:</span>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Spec</th>\n<th>Effect</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>:latex</code> or <code>:inline</code></td>\n<td>Force inline LaTeX</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>:block</code></td>\n<td>Force display-mode LaTeX ($<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(...||)</marimo-tex>$)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>:text</code> or <code>:unicode</code></td>\n<td>Force plain text (no LaTeX)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>:.3f</code>, <code>:+.2f</code>, etc.</td>\n<td>Standard Python numeric formatting</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "BYtC",
      "code_hash": "64c10197c6341668487c7baab0f02e4e",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Numeric format specs:</strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Pi to 3 decimals: 3.142</li>\n<li>Signed float: +2.5</li>\n<li>Percentage: 87.5%</li>\n<li>Scientific: 6.022e+23</li>\n<li>Integer formatting: 1,234,567</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Numeric specs on GA scalars:</strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Norm of v (raw): 3.7416573867739413</li>\n<li>Norm of v (3 dp): 3.742</li>\n<li>Norm\u00b2 of v (1 dp): 14.0</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>GA format specs:</strong></span>\n<ul>\n<li>Auto (default): <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(3 e_{1} + 2 e_{2} - e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>Explicit inline: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(3 e_{1} + 2 e_{2} - e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>Block display: </li>\n</ul>\n<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||[3 e_{1} + 2 e_{2} - e_{3}||]</marimo-tex><ul>\n<li>Unicode text: 3e\u2081 + 2e\u2082 - e\u2083</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "RGSE",
      "code_hash": "63942bb96a17fce40e51bd8edd6d32cc",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"format-specs-on-multivectors\">Format Specs on Multivectors</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">When you apply a numeric format spec like <code>:.3f</code> to a multivector,\n<strong>every coefficient</strong> is formatted \u2014 including \u00b11. The default display\ndrops the <code>1</code> (writing <code>e\u2081</code> instead of <code>1e\u2081</code>), but an explicit format\nspec shows all coefficients literally. This is intentional: if you're\nasking for 3 decimal places, you want to inspect the actual values.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Kclp",
      "code_hash": "35fefa99e458b7997f6e5d1a8ec947af",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><ul>\n<li>Default (drop-1 sugar): <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(1.006 e_{1} + 3.462 e_{2} - e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>With <code>:.3f</code> (all coefficients shown): <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(1.006 e_{1} + 3.462 e_{2} - 1.000 e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li>With <code>:.1f</code>: <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(1.0 e_{1} + 3.5 e_{2} - 1.0 e_{3}||)</marimo-tex></li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Notice <code>-e\u2083</code> vs <code>-1.000e\u2083</code> \u2014 the format spec forces explicit coefficients\nso you can verify whether a value is exactly 1.0 or just close to it.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "emfo",
      "code_hash": "a6188a25542334f2c79b3aa20d62861e",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"conversion-flags\">Conversion Flags</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Standard Python conversion flags (<code>!s</code>, <code>!r</code>, <code>!a</code>) force text mode,\nbypassing LaTeX rendering. Useful for debugging.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
